content:
The gray did soften 'neath golden flame;
the rainbow lean'd in tender arc;
& sky became a poet's heart, undone.

‘..Seldom,
In admiration of ‘em..;
Hwæt thou’ve in thy mind,
dunno see in thy eyes;
Hwæt thou’re saying,
dunno see in thy mind..’

The most idyllic aeon is with love;
The most antagonistic abyss is with hate;
So be a philophile & a xenophobic.

Tale of love is settled in the moon;
Beauty is equally fictionalised with the moon;
Every phase has its zestful sway of the moon
To make us fond of the moon...

The tranquility of night,
while gazing at the moon and stars,
brings placidity to the heart.

Sometimes having no reason for reasoning is
better than having some reasons;
such an unconditional state.
